Sec. 4.5. Chapter 209 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
thereto a new section to read as follows:
The Director may establish, in coordination with the Division
of Forestry of the State Department of Conservation and Natural
Resources, a transitional housing program to provide training in
forestry management and conservation for offenders who:
1. Are committed to the custody of the Department and
eligible for assignment to an institution or facility of minimum
security pursuant to the provisions of NRS 209.481; and
